"The ability to tell your own story, in words or images, is already a victory, already a revolt.\n\n- Rebecca Solnit, Men Explain Things to Me\n|\nIf we can't write diversity into sci-fi, then what's the point? You don't create new worlds to give them all the same limits of the old ones.\n\n- Jane\n|\nNow that she had nothing to lose, she was free.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, Eleven Minutes\n|\nDiscussion is impossible with someone who claims not to seek the truth, but already to possess it.\n\n- Romain Rolland, Above the Battle\n|\nEvery reader exists to ensure for a certain book a modest immortality. Reading is, in this sense, a ritual of rebirth.\n\n- Alberto Manguel, The Library at Night\n|\nWith the greatest force within, you can go farther.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWalking around nude in front of humans was not a good way to keep a low profile with the community. It was an excellent way to make new friends, though.\n\n- Rachel Vincent, Rogue\n|\nThis is your life, and its ending one minute at a time.\n\n- Chuck Palahniuk, Fight Club\n|\nBlack Moms create magic, so that makes me magical.\n\n- Stephanie\n|\nIf I feel physically as if the top of my head were taken off, I know that is poetry.\n\n- Emily\n|\nHell, any game that gives its players guns is probably not the kind that'll ever really let you go free.\n\n- Jeanne Ryan, Nerve\n|\nIn as much time as it takes to smoke a cigarette, a person's life was changed forever.\n\n- Karen McQuestion, A Scattered Life\n|\nLife, is a chess game you win or loose, but just keep playing.\n\n- Auliq\n|\nWhen it came to adults, it was better not to talk. They had a way of hearing one thing and processing it as something else. No reason to give them an excuse to hurt you.\n\n- Alexandra Bracken, The Darkest Minds\n|\nWhere would his torture be, indeed, if at every step the hope of succeeding upheld him?\n\n- Albert\n|\nThe only thing that makes life possible is permanent, intolerable uncertainty: not knowing what comes next.\n\n- Ursula K. Le Guin, The Left Hand of Darkness\n|\nIf you live in Fear, Success will disappear.\n\n- RVM\n|\nIt's only in drugs or death we'll see anything new, and death is just too controlling.\n\n- Chuck Palahniuk, Survivor\n|\nThe face is the mirror of the mind, and eyes without speaking confess the secrets of the heart.\n\n- Jerome\n|\nBut thoughts the slave of life, and life, Time’s fool,And Time, that takes survey of all the world,Must have a stop.\n\n- William Shakespeare, King Henry IV, Part 1\n|\nUnknowns in life are adventures, avoid calling them fears.\n\n- Haritha\n|\nGiven the choice between the experience of pain and nothing, I would choose pain.\n\n- William Faulkner, The Wild Palms\n|\nOf course, freedom is not free. Taxpayers pay for it.\n\n- Zarina\n|\nLife isn’t meant to be lived perfectly…but merely to be LIVED. Boldly, wildly, beautifully, uncertainly, imperfectly, magically LIVED.\n\n- Mandy Hale, The Single Woman: Life, Love, and a Dash of Sass\n|\nWhen we love, we always strive to become better than we are. When we strive to become better than we are, everything around us becomes better too.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, The Alchemist\n|\nIt frightens me, the awful truth, of how sweet life can be...\n\n- Bob\n|\nThe more you look into and understand yourself, the less judgmental you become towards others.\n\n- Tariq\n|\nOh sorry, I was taking life seriously.\n\n- Bill\n|\nLoving is more important than living; without love, life has no meaning.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nAccording to just about every poll on happiness, people on the Left are generally less happy than conservatives.\n\n- Dennis Prager, Still the Best Hope: Why the World Needs American Values to Triumph\n|\nDo not give them a candle to light the way, teach them how to make fire instead. That is the meaning of enlightenment.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nFaith in God is optional, but faith in the self – in the spirit within, is imperative.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Principia Humanitas\n|\nThe dead could only speak through the mouths of those left behind, and through the signs they left scattered behind them.\n\n- Robert Galbraith, The Cuckoo's Calling\n|\nSadly, I hate foreigners. And Americans. And animals. And flora, and some fauna. Also the magma that is the very core of this our mother earth. I'm full o' hate!\n\n- Joss\n|\nMy earnest desire for you has brought me to a point, where the life I've imagined we shall have, seems like a distant memory.\n\n- A.D.\n|\nIt's the truth, even if it didn't happen......if they don't exist, how can a man see them?\n\n- Ken Kesey, One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest\n|\nMany people want to live in an alternate world. As a writer, it’s my job to put them there.\n\n- Devlin\n|\nThey had, finally, the only thing anyone really wants in life: someone to hold your hand when you die.\n\n- Lorrie Moore, Anagrams\n|\nCyber trolls' deceptive manipulative, political power play, duplicity and devious hypocrisy cannot equate to true friendship.~ Angelica Hopes, K.H. Trilogy\n\n- Angelica\n|\nWhen you are searching for knowledge, knowledge is also searching for you.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThe more time you invest into your land of promise, the more productive the land becomes for you.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nWrite it. Shoot it. Publish it. Crochet it, sauté it, whatever. MAKE.\n\n- Joss\n|\nIf we open our mind, doors will open without keys.\n\n- Alin\n|\nWithout education, there will be no knowledge. Without knowledge, how can there be success?\n\n- Debasish\n|\nLet them shoot us in the head,My blood will grow rootsand will blossom.\n\n- Visar Zhiti, The Condemned Apple: Selected Poetry\n|\nIf there’s a takeaway from working here, it’s an understand that, as bioorganisms, we are a walking time bomb programed for cellular self-destruction. Not if, when.\n\n- Laurie Nadel, Dancing with the Wind: A True Story of Zen in the Art of Windsurfing\n|\nMoney can't buy happiness, but it certainly is a stress reliever.\n\n- Besa\n|\nThe greatest gift you can give to someone is your heart; because when you give your heart, you are giving your most prized possession.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nWealth is not often a byproduct of hard work or superior intelligence, but often wealth is a byproduct of a purpose oriented abundant mentality.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nShe stopped at the desk and held up a can for his view. 'This looks like an ordinary hairspray can, right?''Of course.' he said though he had no idea what hairspray was.\n\n- Gena Showalter, Heart of the Dragon\n|\nThere was, I found, always more to learn.\n\n- David Halberstam, The Best and the Brightest\n|\nI've come to realize that sometimes, what you love most is what you have to fight the hardest to keep.\n\n- Kirsten Hubbard, Wanderlove\n|\nIn the marketing society, we seek fulfillment but settle for abundance. Prisoners of plenty, we have the freedom to consume in stead of our freedom to find our place in the world.\n\n- Clive Hamilton, Growth Fetish\n|\nWhat's going on?' Newt asked, looking back and forth between Thomas and Aris. 'Why're you guys looking at each other like you just fell in love?\n\n- James Dashner, The Scorch Trials\n|\nEmotions can become habits - she said haltingly as she wiped her eyes. But habits can be changed'.\n\n- Debbie Macomber, Twenty Wishes\n|\nGrowth is ugly, it's hideous, it's all the things we don't like but my god, once you walk through the fire of confusion you will feel burning passion within your flame.\n\n- Nikki\n|\nOne loves truly only once in a lifetime, Julian, even if one isn’t aware of it.\n\n- Carlos Ruiz Zafón, The Shadow of the Wind\n|\nOnly Give up,When Your Hearts Gives up.(Don't Give up, till your Last Breath)\n\n- Fahad\n|\nIt is as if Little Red Riding Hood had asked the wolf: 'Dear Grandmother, what is the truth for?' And the wolf had replied: 'The truth helps me tell you better lies.\n\n- Sara Castro-Klarén, Understanding Mario Vargas Llosa\n|\nCreate a wisdom and share it with others; in return, don’t wait for anything, not even a simple thanks, because expecting something in return does not belong to the wisdom!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nThe trick is to learn from your mistakes, and have the courage to be true to your heart.\n\n- Cinderpelt, Warriors: The Darkest Hour\n|\nI am afraid. Not of life, or death, or nothingness, but of wasting it as if I had never been.\n\n- Daniel Keyes, Flowers for Algernon\n|\nReligions are often state-protected nurseries of pseudoscience, although there's no reason why religions have to play that role. In a way, it's an artefact from times long gone.\n\n- Carl\n|\nThe devil’s agents may be of flesh and blood, may they not?\n\n- Arthur Conan Doyle, The Hound of the Baskervilles\n|\nSince God is truth, a contempt for truth is equally a contempt for God.\n\n- Gordon H. Clark, A Christian Philosophy of Education\n|\nBefore you can successfully make friends with others, first you have to become your own friend.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nWe should gather all the good and true principles in the world and treasure them up, or we shall not come out true Mormons.\n\n- Joseph Smith, Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Joseph Smith\n|\nThe more you create great music, the more it makes you eager to create more and more\n\n- Sami\n|\nLove is your greatest asset, fear is your greatest liability, and joy is your greatest reward.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nHer fear was strong, but her need for the truth was stronger.\n\n- Jennifer Donnelly, These Shallow Graves\n|\ntruth, like gold, is to be obtained not by its growth, but by washing away from it all that is not gold.\n\n- Leo\n|\nJust because you're in a situation, doesn't mean you have to be that situation. You're not the situation you're in!\n\n- K.M. Johnson, Knowing the Struggle Is Over!\n|\nLife is made up of Moments. Moments create Days, days create Months, months create Years, years create LIFE. Lose the Moment and you lose Life.\n\n- RVM\n|\nIt's funny, how one can look back on a sorrow one thought one might well die of at the time, and know that one had not yet reckoned the tenth part of true grief.\n\n- Jacqueline Carey, Kushiel's Dart\n|\nPactum serva' - 'Keep the faith\n\n- Horace\n|\nThe way you live your day is a sentence in the story of your life. Each day you make the choice whether the sentence ends with a period, question mark, or exclamation point.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nLearn when to talk and when to listen. If you're unsure, listen.\n\n- J. Kyle McNeal, Birthrights\n|\nFear can only grow in darkness. Once you face fear with light, you win.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nSeekers, what are you seeking? Why aren't you happy just to be alive?\n\n- Marty\n|\nHope is the companion of power, and mother of success; for who so hopes strongly has within him the gift of miracles.\n\n- Samuel\n|\nIf you think fate is fickle, try tempting it\n\n- S. Spencer Baker, Slabscape: Reset\n|\nFarewell is said by the living, in life, every day. It is said with love and friendship, with the affirmation that the memories are lasting if the flesh is not.\n\n- R.A. Salvatore, The Legacy\n|\nHatred is a burden that can hunt you day by day, robbing you off your personal joy in broad day light.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Leaders' Frontpage: Leadership Insights from 21 Martin Luther King Jr. Thoughts\n|\nIn a village where everyone has only one leg, the biped will hop about more lamely than anyone else, if he knows what is good for him.\n\n- Idries Shah, Knowing How to Know: A Practical Philosophy in the Sufi Tradition\n|\nDo not live for emptiness, do not waste your evaporating life pursuing the vanities of life.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nEllie: 'You could lie to me. You could tell me to be encouraged, that good will triumph over evil.'Richard: 'Good will triumph over evil.'Ellie: 'Liar.\n\n- Joan Bauer, Squashed\n|\nWhen life hands you lemons, get yourself some limes because life can't be trusted.\n\n- -\n|\nHappiness should never be your ultimate goal as you can experience it everyday, it’s a matter of choice\n\n- Harrish\n|\nSuccess is...knowing your purpose in life,growing to reach your maximum potential, andsowing seeds that benefit others.\n\n- John\n|\nThe Guide says there is an art to flying', said Ford, 'or rather a knack. The knack lies in learning how to throw yourself at the ground and miss.\n\n- Douglas Adams, Life, the Universe and Everything\n|\nbe a good listener, don't judge and don't put boundaries on someone else's grief.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, The Storyteller\n|\nNothing remains forever, only thing that remain forever is romantically stupid word forever.\n\n- Santosh Kalwar, Quote Me Everyday\n|\nO my love, my wife!Death, that hath suck'd the honey of thy breathHath had no power yet upon thy beauty.\n\n- William Shakespeare, Romeo and Juliet\n|\nMan may fall and fail, but God is always right. Man may die and perish, but God is always alive.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Become a Better You\n|\nThe more we see ourselves as a vibrant, successful, inspiring person who boldly declares and manifests her vision, the more we become just that.\n\n- Kristi\n|\nI'm the kind of boy that can fall in love with any girl because I love with the heart, not the eyes.\n\n- Niall\n|\nIf during the day, a person did not do anything about his purpose and calling, he did nothing at all\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWhen you have faults, do not fear to abandon them.\n\n- Confucius\n|\nThe future belongs to all who, refusing to look back at the past move ahead with the clock as it ticks.\n\n- Odo Simon Agbo, The Dancing Sun\n|\nYou said we all want there to be more than this! Well, there's always more than this. There's always something you don't know.\n\n- Patrick Ness, More Than This"